Saturday, 14 July 2018 – The Joint Constitutional Review Committee (CRC) will on Tuesday and Wednesday respectively re-start its public hearings into a possible review of section 25 of the Constitution. A delegation of the (CRC) will on Tuesday begin with hearings in the North West whilst the other delegation will start on Wednesday in KwaZulu-Natal.
	
	The committee was instructed by the National Assembly and the National Council of Provinces to ascertain whether a review of section 25 of the Constitution and other clauses are necessary, to make it possible for the state to expropriate land in the public interest without compensation, and propose the necessary constitutional amendments where necessary. The committee already held hearings in the Northern Cape, Limpopo, Free State and Mpumalanga. Find the programme for North West and KwaZulu-Natal below. Members of the media intending to attend the hearings in the North West should please send their details (name, media house and contact details) to fndenze@parliament.gov.za and those who want to attend hearings in KwaZulu-Natal can contact sugovender@parliament.gov.za. Please find the link for the updated full programme for the public hearings:
	https://tinyurl.com/yb9yvalx.
	
